Stores API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

AdminGetRevenueForStore
GET | Returns: CEFActionResponse<decimal> | Path: /Stores/Store/Current/Revenue/{Days}

Use to get the current store's revenue (limited to store admins)

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
Days int path Yes Not Set!

TypeScript Example

var days: number = this.someValue1;
this.cvApi.stores.AdminGetRevenueForStore(days).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

AdminGetSalesCountForStore
GET | Returns: CEFActionResponse<decimal> | Path: /Stores/Store/Current/SalesCount

Use to get the current store's sales count by type (Order, Invoice, etc.) and Status (pending, shipped, void, approved, etc.) (limited to store admins)

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
Type string query Yes Filter to the sales type (Quote, Order, Invoice)
Status string query Yes Filter to a single status

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AdminGetSalesCountForStoreDto>{
	Type: this.someValue1, // string 
	Status: this.someValue2, // string 
};
this.cvApi.stores.AdminGetSalesCountForStore(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

AdminGetSalesCountMultipleStatusesForStore
POST | Returns: CEFActionResponse<decimal> | Path: /Stores/Store/Current/SalesCount

Use to get the current store's sales count by type (Order, Invoice, etc.) and Status (pending, shipped, void, approved, etc.) (limited to store admins)

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
Type string body Yes Filter to the sales type (Quote, Order, Invoice)
Statuses string body Yes Filter to any of these statuses

TypeScript Example

var dto = <api.AdminGetSalesCountMultipleStatusesForStoreDto>{
	Type: this.someValue1, // string 
	Statuses: this.someValue2, // string 
};
this.cvApi.stores.AdminGetSalesCountMultipleStatusesForStore(dto).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

GetStores
GET | Returns: StorePagedResults | Path: /Stores/Stores

Use to get a list of stores

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
HostUrl string query No Host URL for search
ZipCode string query No Origin ZipCode from which you extending by radius to find entities
Latitude double? query No Origin Latitude from which you extending by radius to find entities
Longitude double? query No Origin Longitude from which you extending by radius to find entities
Radius int? query No The number of units to extend in a radius from the center of the Origin ZipCode
Units string query No The unit of measure for the radius. Must be either mi (miles) or km (kilometers). Default is mi.
RegionID int? query No This is the Region where the store is located.
StoreContactRegionID int? query No This filters if the store services this region.
CountryID int? query No This is the Country where the store is located.
StoreContactCountryID int? query No This filters if the store services this country.
